Our Trees

Sustainable oil mallee plantations for carbon sequestration and environmental restoration.

At Orgatek, we cultivate oil mallee plantations across Western Australia, creating sustainable ecosystems that sequester carbon while providing valuable resources.

Our carefully managed plantations not only contribute to carbon reduction but also support biodiversity and help restore degraded agricultural lands.

Oil Mallee

Eucalyptus species specifically selected for their high oil content and carbon sequestration capabilities. These trees are drought-resistant and thrive in Western Australia's climate.

Biodiversity Support

Our plantations create habitats for native wildlife and support local ecosystems. We implement sustainable practices that promote biodiversity while maintaining productive land use.

Oil Mallee Plantations

Our oil mallee plantations are carefully managed to maximize carbon sequestration while producing valuable resources. These trees are specifically chosen for their ability to thrive in Western Australia's climate and their high oil content, making them perfect for both environmental and commercial purposes.

Learn about our plantations

Environmental Impact

Our tree plantations play a crucial role in environmental restoration and carbon sequestration. By carefully managing our plantations, we create sustainable ecosystems that support biodiversity, improve soil health, and contribute to climate change mitigation.
